<span id="Introduction"></span>
== Einführung ==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The '''BulletDesigner Workbench''' is an external workbench for FreeCAD that provides parametric bullet and projectile design with integrated ballistic calculations, material database, and export capabilities.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
[[Image:BulletDesigner_screenshot.png|800px]]
</div>

<span id="Features"></span>
== Funktionen ==

<span id="Bullet_design"></span>
=== Kugelentwurf ===

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* Fully parametric bullet geometry with live preview.
* Multiple bullet types: land-riding, flat-base, boat-tail, hollow-point.
* Ogive profiles: tangent, secant, elliptical with configurable caliber ratios.
* Configurable driving bands (number, spacing, length).
</div>

<span id="Ballistic_calculations"></span>
=== Ballistische Berechnungen ===

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* Stability factor (Miller's formula with velocity correction).
* Ballistic coefficient (G1, estimated G7).
* Sectional density.
* Recommended twist rate (Greenhill formula).
* Trajectory simulation with transonic zone detection.
* Spin drift estimation (Litz empirical formula).
</div>

<span id="Other"></span>
=== Andere ===

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* Built-in material database (copper, brass, gilding metal, lead, tungsten, steel).
* Export to STEP and STL for manufacturing or 3D printing.
</div>

== Installation ==

Nutze den [[Std_AddonMgr/de|FreeCAD Addon-Manager]]:

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Open FreeCAD.
# Go to {{MenuCommand|Tools → Addon Manager}}.
# Search for '''BulletDesigner'''.
# Click '''Install''' and restart FreeCAD.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Manual installation: clone or download the repository and copy the {{FileName|BulletDesigner}} folder to your FreeCAD Mod directory:
* '''Linux''': {{FileName|~/.FreeCAD/Mod/}}.
* '''Windows''': {{FileName|C:\Users\<username>\AppData\Roaming\FreeCAD\Mod\}}.
* '''macOS''': {{FileName|~/Library/Preferences/FreeCAD/Mod/}}.
</div>

<span id="Usage"></span>
== Anwendung ==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
=== Creating a bullet ===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Switch to the '''BulletDesigner''' workbench.
# Click {{Button|Create Bullet}} or use {{MenuCommand|Bullet Designer → Create → Create Bullet}}.
# Adjust parameters in the tabbed task panel:
#* '''Basic''': diameter, length, weight.
#* '''Ogive''': type, caliber ratio, meplat diameter.
#* '''Bands''': number, length, spacing.
#* '''Base''': flat or boat tail configuration.
#* '''Material''': material selection and density.
# Enable '''Live Preview''' to see real-time updates.
# Click {{Button|OK}} to generate the bullet.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
=== Ballistic calculator ===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Select a bullet object (optional — auto-fills parameters).
# Click {{Button|Ballistic Calculator}}.
# Enter twist rate, muzzle velocity, and atmospheric conditions.
# Click {{Button|Calculate}}.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Results include stability factor (Sg), BC, sectional density, and recommended twist rate.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
{{Emphasis|Driving bands must fit within the body length (total length minus ogive and boat tail length), or the solid will not be generated.}}
</div>

<span id="Ballistic_formulas"></span>
== Ballistische Formeln ==

<span id="Stability_factor_(Miller)"></span>
=== Stabilitätsfaktor (Miller) ===

:<math>S_g = \frac{30 \times m}{t^2 \times d^3 \times l \times (1 + l^2)} \times \left(\frac{V}{2800}\right)^{1/3}</math>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Thresholds:
* Monolithic copper/brass: S<sub>g</sub> ≥ 1.8.
* Lead-core: S<sub>g</sub> ≥ 1.5.
</div>

<span id="Ballistic_coefficient_(G1)"></span>
=== Ballistischer Koeffizient (G1) ===

:<math>BC = \frac{SD}{i}</math>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Where SD = sectional density and ''i'' = form factor (tangent: 0.85, secant: 0.80, elliptical: 0.75).
</div>

<span id="Sectional_density"></span>
=== Sektionsdichte ===

:<math>SD = \frac{W_{lbs}}{d_{in}^2}</math>

<span id="Requirements"></span>
==Voraussetzungen==

* FreeCAD 0.21 oder später.
* Python 3.8 oder später.
* PySide2 (in FreeCAD enthalten).

